                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_astær" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>astær</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подкладка</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>lining</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæsonastær</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подкладка на спине (у черкески и пр.)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>lining on the back (for Circassian clothes, etc.)</q></abv:tr></sense></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>astar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>āstar</w> <gloss><q>подкладка</q></gloss></mentioned>. Взаимоотношения персидского и тюркского слов не вполне ясны (см.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>). Нет препятствий осетинское слово вместе с персидским возводить к основе %i*star-%i ‘стлать’, сращенной с префиксом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>āstara-</w> <gloss><q>подстилка</q></gloss></mentioned>; см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stæryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astæryn"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>astar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>āstar</w> <gloss><q>lining</q></gloss></mentioned>. The relationship between Persian and Turkic words is not entirely clear (see: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Horn._Gr."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."/><biblScope>7</biblScope></bibl>). There are no obstacles to trace back the Ossetian word, together with the Persian one, to %i*star-%i ‘to form ', fused with the prefix <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>āstara-</w> <gloss><q>underlay</q></gloss></mentioned>; see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_stæryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astæryn"/>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>